  <tr> 
     <td width="100%" height="30" align="center" class="big" bgcolor="#A34D1E"> Ring of Thule&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:content@gameznet.com?subject=Quest Info : ">Submit Info</a></font> </td> 
   </tr> 
  <tr bgcolor="#4A2A12"> 
     <td align="left"> <b><font color=#d2d200>Classes:</font></b>&nbsp;Any<br> 
      <b><font color=#d2d200>Recommended Level:</b></font>&nbsp;60<br> 
       
      <b><font color=#d2d200>Quest Rating:</b></font>&nbsp;Very Good&nbsp;(8) <br> 
      <br> 
      <b>Reward(s):</b> 
      <br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7311" alt="Fright Imbued Battlestaff">Fright Imbued Battlestaff</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7312" alt="Dread Coronet">Dread Coronet</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7684" alt="Bladed Thulian Eviscerator">Bladed Thulian Eviscerator</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7685" alt="Talisman of Fright">Talisman of Fright</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7686" alt="Terror Forged Short Sword">Terror Forged Short Sword</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=7687" alt="Scalecracker">Scalecracker</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=8133" alt="Ring of Dreadful Dreams">Ring of Dreadful Dreams</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=8696" alt="Mantle of Paralyzing Fright">Mantle of Paralyzing Fright</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=8697" alt="Feartouched Greatsword">Feartouched Greatsword</a><br>&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=12780" alt="Pearl of Dread">Pearl of Dread</a>      <br>
 
      <br> 
      <b><font color=#d2d200>Starting NPC:</b></font>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/beast.php?mob=A Thul Taw Ew High Priest">A Thul Taw Ew High Priest</a> 
       
      <br> 
      <b><font color=#d2d200>Starting Zone:</b></font>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/zone.php?name=Cazic Thule">Cazic Thule</a> 
       
      <br> 
      <br> 
      <b>Related NPCs:</b> <br> 
&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/beast.php?mob=Avatar of Fear">Avatar of Fear</a> 
       
      <br> 
&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/quest.php?name=Avatar of Fright">Avatar of Fright</a> 
       
      <br> 
&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/quest.php?name=Avatar of Terror">Avatar of Terror</a> 
       
      <br> 
      <br> 
      <b>Related Items:</b> 
       
      <br> 
      <br> 
      <b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font> <br> 
      This ring event is initiated by killing the High Priest in Cazic Thule(in the globe room). There is a thread on this topic at <a href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=13099.topic">The Safehouse</a>.<br />
<br />
Once the High Priest is killed the four untargetable lizards will explode, doing AE damage to anyone near them. At that point the Avatar of Fear will spawn, but he will be untargetable. He will spawn a random set of mobs from the Plane of Fear(Amygdalans, etc) in sets of four. These mobs will occasionally drop Runes which can be turned in to a female NPC who is in the event area. When turned in to her she will restore everyoen in the rooms hit points and mana to full. Be warned though, that this spell aggros your pets. So either do not summon pets or put the pets on hold and then back them off after you do this. You may only turn in three runes during the battle so use them wisely.<br />
<br />
The waves will come four at at a time, and in the middle of these waves he will spawn the mini-bosses from fear(Fright, Terror and Dread), one at a time. The mini-bosses will be untargetable at first. <br />
<br />
At some point the mini-bosses will become targetable one at a time. Once one mini-boss is killed the next will become targetable and attack. This whole time the Avatar of Fear will continue walking around the room and spawning additional mobs four at a time. Crowd control and killing adds quickly is extremely important here.<br />
<br />
After Terror(the final mini-boss) is dead the Avatar of Fear will become taretable and attack. His special attack i a 1000 damage AE spell. <br />
<br />
The reward for this ring is the loot tables of the bosses/mini-bosses. </td> 
   </tr> 
